tum.dss.thesis.knapsack

Class ItemsetHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • tum.dss.thesis.lsframework.AbstractItemsetHandler
      • tum.dss.thesis.knapsack.ItemsetHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, ItemsetHandlerInterface

    public class ItemsetHandler
extends AbstractItemsetHandler
    Handles single kind of items for the multi-unit auction / knapsack problem. The following is equivalent: index = quantity = |subsets|.
    Author:
    Florian Stallmann
    See Also:

      • isSubset

        public boolean isSubset(int k,
                        int j)
        Description copied from interface: ItemsetHandlerInterface
        Checks if set with index k is a subset of set with index j.
        • e.g. k=3, j=0: true as {A} is subset of {A,A}
        • e.g. k=3, j=1: true as {A} is subset of {A,B,C}
        • e.g. k=3, j=3: false as {A,A} is not a real subset of {A,A}
        Parameters:
        k - index of subset.
        j - index of superset.
        Returns:
        true if k ⊂ j, false otherwise.

      • isSuperset

        public boolean isSuperset(int k,
                          int j)
        Description copied from interface: ItemsetHandlerInterface
        Checks if set with index k is a superset of set with index j.
        • e.g. k=0, j=3: true as {A,A} is superset of {A}
        • e.g. k=1, j=3: true as {A,B,C} is superset of {A}
        • e.g. k=3, j=3: false as {A,A} is not a real superset of {A,A}
        Parameters:
        k - index of superset.
        j - index of subset.
        Returns:
        true if k ⊃ j, false otherwise.
